I invented really nothing in the hardware area.
So thanks to mibox.org (ucapps.de) and sparkfun for providing all the hardware information i use.

. The LCD wiring is a classic HD44780 one :
http://www.ucapps.de/mbhp_lcd.html

. Same thing for the EEPROM :
http://www.ucapps.de/mbhp_bankstick.html

. And also for the Encoder and buttons :
http://www.ucapps.de/mbhp_din.html

. The midi comes from sparkfun, schematic here :
http://www.sparkfun.com/products/9595

. And the filter is a 1st order regular RC filter.
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Low-pass_filter

Xavier


